    "It contains 73,257 training and 26,032 test images, each sized 32×32 and labeled into 10 digit classes.",
    "Compared to MNIST, SVHN is more challenging due to background clutter and variation, making it suitable for evaluating robustness under real-world conditions.",
    "• CIFAR-10 Krizhevsky et al. (2009) is a widely used image classification dataset with 60,000 32x32 color images across 10 classes.",
    "The dataset is split into 50,000 training images and 10,000 test images.",
    "• ImageNet-50 Deng et al. (2009) is a 50-class subset of ImageNet for efficiency."
